channel.description: A feed of recent tweets from DevHawk.

item.description: Minor @Neo_Blockchain tool news: Neo 3.3.1 compatible version of my DumpNEF tool is now available. Minor update to generated comments + Neo version bump https://t.co/wTChpq5q8d

We just shipped the latest #NeoBlockchainToolkit for @Neo_Blockchain v3.3.1 last week. Unfortunately, we had to update the Neo.BuildTasks package to address a Neo C# compiler issue. https://t.co/Od0nMhPy2L
Neo.BuildTasks v3.3.23 addresses the issue, fixes a couple bugs, adds new tests and adds a new ContractNameOverride attribute to give developers more control over the generated test code.
https://t.co/maszyFKvJ3
There's also a new doc that describes the various MSBuild properties and items that Neo.BuildTasks uses and provides guidance for upgrading your v3.1 project to v3.3 (mostly removing stuff that's no longer needed)
https://t.co/5WrvYbypLS

@patrickallmond I did 330# squat Tuesday last week, but tweaked my neck. I cycled back to 315# for Friday and 325# on Sunday before taking another run at 330# today. Felt good. 360# deadlift felt significantly less good. I spilled water in my gym bag and my wrist straps were wet. Threw me off.
Today's Workout : 330# squat, 125# overhead, 360# deadlift. 5x5 worksets (3x5 deadlift worksets) #StrongLifts5x5
Mystery bridge, wiped out by landslide right before pandemic https://t.co/XMjlaMbfII
Nice day for a mariners game. Taking bro-in-law, my nephew and my oldest son for tonight's game @ T-Mobile Park https://t.co/i49Xlj5pFW
Today's workout: 315# squats, 120# overhead press, 355# deadlift. 5x5 squat + overhead work sets (3x5 deadlift work sets) #strongLifts5x5
